Mblogger
 Blogger User's tool

Dependency
 Ruby 1.9.1
 gdata 1.1.1
 http://code.google.com/p/gdata-ruby-util/downloads/list

Usage
 # get your BlogID
 $ cd mblogger/bin
 $ ruby191 get-bloggerid.rb
 # =>
 BlogTitle=> your blog title
 BlogURL=> http://xxxxxxx.blogspot.com/
 BlogID => xxxxxxxxx

After edit files "bin/mblogger-config" and "bin/mblogger-run.rb",

[help]
$ ./mblogger-run.rb -h

[get entry in current month]
$ ./mblogger-run.rb -blg-get

[get entry]
$ ./mblogger-run.rb -blg-get 2010-01

[print xml]
$ ./mblogger-run.rb -blg-doc ~/draft.txt

[post entry]
$ ./mblogger-run.rb -blg-post ~/draft.txt

[update entry]
$ ./mblogger-run.rb -blg-up 2010-01-01.txt

[delete entry]
$ ./mblogger-run.rb -blg-del 2010-01-01.txt


[Text]
$ cat draft.txt
--control
yes
--category
test,blogger,music
--title
New Title
--content
test post.
second line.
link line <a href='http://github.com'>git.com</a> ... 

today's bgm
<blockquote>
1, court and spark
2, edith and the kingpin
...
</blockquote>

brank line

<pre>
def hello
  puts "ruby is fun\n"
end
</pre>
last line.


[Alias]
$ vi .bashrc
# add 
 alias 'blogger'='/path/to/mblogger/bin/mblogger-run.rb'

$ source .bashrc
$ blogger -h

